<p><b>Rough Trade</b> was a <a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canadian</a> <a href="/wiki/New_wave_music" title="New wave music">new wave</a> rock band in the 1970s and 1980s, centred on singer <a href="/wiki/Carole_Pope" title="Carole Pope">Carole Pope</a> and multi-instrumentalist Kevan Staples. The band was noted for their provocative lyrics and stage antics; singer Pope often performed in bondage attire, and their 1981 hit "<a href="/wiki/High_School_Confidential_(Rough_Trade_song)" title="High School Confidential (Rough Trade song)">High School Confidential</a>" was one of the first explicitly <a href="/wiki/Lesbian" title="Lesbian">lesbian</a>-themed <a href="/wiki/Top_40" title="Top 40">Top 40</a> hits in the world.</p>
<p></p>
